Citation.sTitle: Liquid-liquid equilibria of ionic liquid 1-(2-methoxyethyl)-3-methylimidazolium bromide + potassium carbonate, potassium phosphate, dipotassium phosphate + water aqueous two-phase systems
Citation.sAbstract: Binodal curves of 1-(2-methoxyethyl)-3-methylimidazolium bromide + potassium carbonate, potassium phosphate, dipotassium phosphate + water aqueous two-phase systems were determined experimentally at T = 288.15, 298.15 and 308.15 K, respectively. Effect of temperature on binodal curves was studied. Two empirical equations were used for reproducing the experimental binodal data. Effective excluded volume (EEV) theory was used to investigate the phase-forming strength of salts PO4^3- greater than HPO4^2- greater than CO3^2-. Additionally, the tie-line data were correlated by the Othmer-Tobias, Bancroft and Setschenow-type equations.
